# TRIBE вЂ” Full Project Implementation Plan

Building the complete TRIBE platform from `tribe_specification.md`. MERN stack + Socket.io + Redis.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MongoDB**: Do you already have a MongoDB instance (Atlas / local)? I'll set up with a `MONGO_URI` env var either way, but knowing helps me configure the connection string.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Redis**: Do you have Redis running locally, or should I use an in-memory fallback for development? Redis is needed for Socket.io scaling and BullMQ job queues. For local dev, I can mock these or use `ioredis` pointed at `localhost:6379`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **File Storage**: For development, should I use local file storage (multer to disk) and swap to S3/Cloudinary later? Or do you have S3/Cloudinary credentials ready?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope**: This is a very large platform. I recommend building in **4 phases**, shipping a working app after Phase 1 (auth + lobbies + chat + basic feed). Do you want me to build all 4 phases now, or ship Phase 1 first so you can see it running?

---

