## Phase 1: Foundation & Core Loop (Build First)
*Goal: A working app where users can register, browse lobbies, create lobbies, request to join, get approved, and chat вЂ” all in real-time.*

### 1A вЂ” Project Scaffolding
- Initialize `server/` with Express, Mongoose, Socket.io, dotenv, cors, helmet
- Initialize `client/` with Vite + React (no TypeScript for speed)
- Set up `.env` with `MONGO_URI`, `JWT_SECRET`, `REDIS_URL`, `PORT`
- Configure proxy/CORS between client and server

### 1B вЂ” Design System & Global CSS
- Create `index.css` with all design tokens from Section 2.2 (Warm Precision theme)
- Import Google Fonts (Outfit, Inter, JetBrains Mono)
- Dark/light mode CSS variables with `[data-theme="dark"]` selector
- Base component styles (buttons, cards, inputs, badges, modals)
- Skeleton loading animation keyframes

### 1C вЂ” Database Models (All 10)
- User, Lobby, JoinRequest, Message, Notification, Squad, Challenge, Venue, TimeSlot, Tournament
- All indexes defined in schema files
- `sportConfig.js` validation map

### 1D вЂ” Auth System
- Register/Login routes + controllers
- JWT middleware (cookie-based httpOnly)
- RBAC middleware (roles array check)
- Rate limiting middleware
- Frontend: AuthContext, Login page, Register page, protected routes

### 1E вЂ” Lobby CRUD + Feed
- Create, read, update, close, delete lobby
- Sport validation on create
- Feed API with cursor pagination + sport/location filters
- Frontend: Feed page with LobbyCards, filters, infinite scroll
- Frontend: LobbyCreate multi-step form
- Frontend: LobbyDetail page (organizer vs player view)

### 1F вЂ” Join Request System
- Request to join, approve, reject, cancel, dropout endpoints
- Atomic `findOneAndUpdate` with slot guard
- Duplicate prevention (compound index)
- Frontend: Request button on lobby cards, approve/reject UI for organizers

### 1G вЂ” Real-Time Socket.io
- Socket.io server setup with room-based architecture
- JWT auth on socket handshake
- Lobby room join/leave
- `roster_updated`, `lobby_locked`, `request_received`, `player_dropped` events
- Frontend: SocketContext, live feed updates, live lobby state

### 1H вЂ” In-Lobby Chat
- Messages collection CRUD
- Paginated `GET /lobbies/:id/messages`
- Socket.io `new_message` event broadcast within lobby room
- Frontend: ChatPanel component with real-time messages

### 1I вЂ” Landing Page
- Hero section with the Warm Precision design
- "How it Works" section
- CTA to login/register
- Responsive layout

---

## Phase 2: Venues & Squads
*Goal: Full venue booking ecosystem and squad/challenge system.*

### 2A вЂ” Venue System
- Venue model with sport-specific pitches
- TimeSlot collection with all CRUD
- Venue directory, profile, booking endpoints
- Booking cancellation with 24h rule
- Frontend: VenueDirectory, VenueProfile, booking flow in LobbyCreate

### 2B вЂ” Venue Owner Dashboard
- Dashboard page with booking calendar grid
- Pitch & slot management UI
- Booking history & analytics
- Instant Book vs Request to Book toggle
- Socket.io venue events (booking_received, booking_confirmed, booking_cancelled)

### 2C вЂ” Squad System
- Squad CRUD + discovery endpoints
- Squad profile page
- Squad invite system
- Frontend: SquadDiscovery, SquadProfile pages

### 2D вЂ” Squad vs. Squad Challenges
- Challenge collection CRUD
- Accept в†’ auto-create lobby workflow
- Challenge expiry via BullMQ
- Socket.io challenge events
- Frontend: Challenge browsing, posting, accepting

---

## Phase 3: Advanced Features
*Goal: Waitlists, ringer alerts, tournaments, notifications.*

### 3A вЂ” Waitlist & Ringer System
- Waitlist join/promotion logic
- BullMQ delayed jobs for 5-minute promotion timer
- Ringer alert geoproximity queries
- Frontend: Waitlist UI, ringer toggle, ringer alert notifications

### 3B вЂ” Lobby Expiry System
- BullMQ recurring job for lobby transitions
- Status enum (COMPLETED, EXPIRED) handling
- Feed exclusion logic

### 3C вЂ” Notification System
- Notification collection CRUD
- In-app notification center
- Notification preferences (per-channel, per-type)
- Frontend: NotificationDropdown, notification preferences in profile

### 3D вЂ” Tournament System
- Tournament CRUD + registration
- Bracket generation logic (4 formats)
- Tournament matches as linked lobbies
- Frontend: TournamentDirectory, TournamentDetail with bracket visualization

---

## Phase 4: Admin & Polish
*Goal: Admin panel, file uploads, final polish.*

### 4A вЂ” Admin Dashboard
- Metrics API (active lobbies, users, bookings)
- Venue verification queue
- User ban system
- Frontend: AdminDashboard page

### 4B вЂ” File Upload System
- S3/Cloudinary presigned URL generation
- Avatar upload on profile
- Venue photo upload
- Squad logo upload

### 4C вЂ” User Profile
- Full profile page with stats, preferences, history
- Notification preferences UI
- Ringer mode toggle
- Match/request history timeline

### 4D вЂ” Responsive & Accessibility Polish
- Mobile-first responsive breakpoints
- Keyboard navigation
- ARIA labels
- Performance optimization (lazy loading, code splitting)

---

## Verification Plan

### Per-Phase Verification
After each phase, I will:
1. **Start the server** and verify no startup errors
2. **Start the client** and verify all pages render
3. **Test API endpoints** with actual HTTP requests
4. **Test real-time features** by opening multiple browser tabs
5. **Verify database** вЂ” check indexes created, documents stored correctly

### Phase 1 Specific Tests
- Register в†’ Login в†’ JWT stored in cookie
- Create lobby в†’ Appears in feed in real-time
- Request to join в†’ Organizer sees notification в†’ Approve в†’ Slot decrements atomically
- Open lobby in 2 tabs в†’ Slot updates appear in both simultaneously
- Send chat message в†’ Appears in real-time for all lobby members
- Attempt duplicate join в†’ Returns 409

---

## Technology Dependencies

### Server (`package.json`)
```
express, mongoose, socket.io, @socket.io/redis-adapter,
jsonwebtoken, bcryptjs, helmet, cors, dotenv,
express-rate-limit, express-validator, ioredis, bullmq
```

### Client (`package.json`)
```
react, react-dom, react-router-dom, axios, socket.io-client
```
*Intentionally minimal frontend dependencies вЂ” no UI library, all custom CSS per the Warm Precision design system.*
